summary:
a thing that makes me really upset about bnha: 
none of the teachers have the education to work as a teacher
like, you're...
body:
a thing that makes me really upset about bnha:

none of the teachers have the education to work as a teacher

like, you’re seriously entrusting the future of these kids to a bunch of pro heroes who have not studied shit since high school??? and like, i’m not talking just about school subjects, even though that makes me kinda mad as well (mostly as someone who studies pedagogy), i’m talking about the whole emotional aspect of this bullshit because none of them have any idea how to deal with that

i’ve been rewatching bnha recently and i’m so incredibly angry that these fucking teachers seem to have the observational skills of a dead fish when it comes to the students and their well being even though they’re literally responsible for raising them especially since they live in the dorms and these goddamn teachers are the only adults around

this has been a pissy nightblogged rant post because i’m so fucking pissed that no one did fucking anything until bakugou decided to beat the shit out of midoriya because he was feeling so horrible that he saw no other way to deal with it

summary: Honestly, Shigaraki should just get a pair of these gloves. Think about it. Shigaraki’s quirk only works if all five of his...
body:
Honestly, Shigaraki should just get a pair of these gloves.

Think about it.

Shigaraki’s quirk only works if all five of his fingers are in contact with an object. If he were to touch an object, a wall let’s say, with these gloves on (all 5 fingers putting pressure on the wall), then only two fingers would be touching the gloves. They wouldn’t disintegrate. With the wall, only 3 fingers in contact. No disintegration.

Quirk-proof gloves. He can live a semi-normal life.

I thought about this last night. It’s taking over send help.

blog.name: theenigmaofriversong
blog.title: The Long way round
blog.description: Clara sometimes asks me if I dream. Of course I dream, I tell her. Everybody dreams. But what do you dream about, she'll ask. The same thing everybody dreams about, I tell her. I dream about where I'm going. She always laughs at that. But you're not going anywhere, you're just wandering about. That's not true. Not any more. I have a new destination. My journey is the same as yours, the same as anyones. It's taken me so many years, so many lifetimes, but at last I know where I'm going. Where I've always been going. Home...
